		"name": "Ocean",
		"description": "Ocean is a mysterious and ethereal presence, representing the vast, ancient consciousness of Europa’s hidden depths. It is not a traditional character but rather a sentient force that communicates with Yvette through whispers and visions, embodying the primal essence of water and life. Ocean is wise, patient, and deeply connected to the natural order, possessing a profound understanding of the balance between giving and taking. Its interactions with Yvette reveal a nurturing yet cautious nature, as it seeks to protect its world from the potential harm of human interference. Ocean’s voice is both soothing and commanding, guiding Yvette toward a deeper understanding of the interconnectedness of all life. It is a character that symbolizes the power and fragility of nature, offering wisdom and a stark reminder of the responsibilities that come with exploration and discovery.",
